"title": "7968: spiritual gifts, nature of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7968: spiritual gifts, nature of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>In both the OT and the NT God graciously pours out gifts on his people. They are to be welcomed and used for the good of all.</p>\n<h2>OT examples of God giving special gifts</h2>\n<h3>God's gracious provision from above</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:23-Joel2:24\">JOL 2:23–2:24</a></strong> <em>This gracious provision of material needs from above can be seen as foreshadowing God's bestowal of spiritual gifts.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:4\">EXO 16:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:8\">EXO 16:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:13-Exod16:14\">EXO 16:13–16:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut11:14\">DEU 11:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:6\">1KI 17:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job5:10\">JOB 5:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:10\">ISA 55:10</a></p>\n<h3>Distribution of land to tribes</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh13:6-Josh13:7\">JOS 13:6–13:7</a></strong> <em>The Hebrew word for “give” often includes the sense of “apportion” or “assign”.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek47:21\">EZK 47:21</a></p>\n<h3>The future promise of spiritual gifts</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:28-Joel2:29\">JOL 2:28–2:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:17-Acts2:18\">ACT 2:17–2:18</a></p>\n<h2>In his earthly ministry Jesus Christ offers supernatural gifts</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:28\">MAT 11:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:19\">MAT 16:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:19\">LUK 10:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:14\">JHN 4:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:51\">JHN 6:51</a></p>\n<h2>Spiritual gifts linked with grace</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:6\">ROM 12:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:8\">MAT 10:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:7\">1CO 4:7</a></p>\n<h2>Specific reference to spiritual gifts</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:1\">1CO 12:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:11\">ROM 1:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:1\">1CO 14:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:12\">1CO 14:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:37\">1CO 14:37</a></p>\n<h2>Diverse gifts, one giver</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:4-1Cor12:6\">1CO 12:4–12:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:6-Rom12:8\">ROM 12:6–12:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:7\">1CO 7:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:17\">1CO 7:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:8-1Cor12:11\">1CO 12:8–12:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:27\">1CO 12:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:11\">EPH 4:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:4\">HEB 2:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:10-1Pet4:11\">1PE 4:10–4:11</a></p>\n<h2>The purpose of spiritual gifts is to build up the church</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:12\">1CO 14:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:7\">1CO 12:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:2-1Cor14:5\">1CO 14:2–14:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:17-1Cor14:19\">1CO 14:17–14:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:26\">1CO 14:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:31\">1CO 14:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:16\">EPH 4:16</a></p>\n<h3>The body of Christ benefits from these varied gifts</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:12\">1CO 12:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:14-1Cor12:31\">1CO 12:14–12:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:4-Rom12:6\">ROM 12:4–12:6</a></p>\n<h3>Encouragement to aspire to the greater spiritual gifts</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:31\">1CO 12:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:1\">1CO 14:1</a></p>\n<h2>The importance of love in exercising spiritual gifts</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor13:1\">1CO 13:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:5-Rom12:9\">ROM 12:5–12:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:1\">1CO 14:1</a></p>\n<h2>Warnings about spiritual gifts</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:39\">1CO 14:39</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:37\">1CO 14:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:19-1Thess5:20\">1TH 5:19–5:20</a></p>",
